ometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert II De Lore was born about 1280, in France as the son of Robert DE LORE. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1280–":"umbes 1280–Surnud","1280–Male":"1280–Surnud","1325–Male":"1325–Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1325":"1325","1250":"1250","Abt 1280":"umbes 1280","1280":"1280","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1280–":"noin 1280–Kuollut","1280–Male":"1280–Kuollut","1325–Male":"1325–Kuollut","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1325":"1325","1250":"1250","Abt 1280":"noin 1280","1280":"1280","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"Abt 1280–":"environ 1280–Décédé","1280–Male":"1280–Décédé","1325–Male":"1325–Décédé","1250–Male":"1250–Décédé","1325":"1325","1250":"1250","Abt 1280":"environ 1280","1280":"1280","France":"France","lifeSummary":"Robert II De Lore est né environ 1280, à France, fils de Robert DE LORE. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"Abt 1280–":"um 1280–Verstorben","1280–Male":"1280–Verstorben","1325–Male":"1325–Verstorben","1250–Male":"1250–Verstorben","1325":"1325","1250":"1250","Abt 1280":"um 1280","1280":"1280","France":"Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Robert II De Lore wurde um 1280 in Frankreich, als Sohn von Robert DE LORE geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"Abt 1280–":"about 1280–Desede","1280–Male":"1280–Desede","1325–Male"